Okay, so I'm looking at this commit related to `mm/memblock.c`.  Initially, I noticed a function, `reserve_bootmem_region`, which was previously defined in `mm/mm_init.c`, but now appears to be in `mm/memblock.c` itself.  The code in `mm/mm_init.c` had the following:

```c
void __meminit reserve_bootmem_region(phys_addr_t start,
				      phys_addr_t end, int nid)
{
	unsigned long pfn;

	for_each_valid_pfn(pfn, PFN_DOWN(start), PFN_UP(end)) {
		struct page *page = pfn_to_page(pfn);

		__init_deferred_page(pfn, nid);

		/*
		 * no need for atomic set_bit because the struct
		 * page is not visible yet so nobody should
		 * access it yet.
		 */
		__SetPageReserved(page);
	}
}
```

Now, the entire `reserve_bootmem_region` function has been moved into `mm/memblock.c` as `memmap_init_reserved_range`. I needed to quickly make sure `mm/memblock.c` includes `<linux/page-flags.h>` either directly or indirectly. It does. I also had to quickly confirm that `__SetPageReserved(page)` is using the non-atomic versions.

Then I realized that `tools/testing/memblock/internal.h` includes some stubs and changes to the macros related to `for_each_valid_pfn`, `init_deferred_page` and `__SetPageReserved`, which have been implemented because `mm/memblock.c` is now using these functions and macros. This must be taken into account when testing.

I checked to see if making the function static in the `mm/memblock.c` file had any architectural issues. It doesn't, because it was only ever used by `memmap_init_reserved_pages()`, which had already been in `mm/memblock.c`.

I also noticed a change in `include/linux/bootmem_info.h`. The comment mentioning `reserve_bootmem_region` and its relationship to `free_bootmem_page` has been dropped. It seems this is because it was "bogus," referring to a function that marks pages as reserved, which is done through `PageReserved()` in other sections of the code.

I had to clarify the scope of `init_deferred_page` function. It seems it is *not* static, as the commit message stated, "Since init_deferred_pages() is not static anymore, move reserve_bootmem_range()..." I need to check to see if this change happened in an earlier commit to this one. The commit changes confirm this:

```c
void __meminit init_deferred_page(unsigned long pfn, int nid)
{
	__init_deferred_page(pfn, nid);
}
```

The function `init_deferred_page` is not static.

I'm checking the declaration and usage of `init_deferred_page`, and it looks like it's declared in `mm/internal.h`.  Since `mm/memblock.c` is also in the `mm/` directory, it is able to include this header. I had to quickly check if `mm/memblock.c` directly includes `mm/internal.h`, but I was pretty sure it did.


